ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This class was immeasurable beneficial to my progress as a student of Arabic, and also a great deal of fun. The material was exciting and enriching, and of course, a very rewarding challenge.Professor Gruendler is an exceptional teacher, and truly brings the language to life, in all of its nuance and color. She is unquestionably knowledgeable and helpful in sharing that knowledge with her students.
Extensive reading in a main classical text, with some related minor texts. Highly recommended with no hesitation.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course was my introduction into Arabic poetic theory, and I learned quite a bit about the subject. It provided me with valuable skills that will no doubt serve me well in the years to come.
The course directly contribute to my area of interest, specifically the application of reader response theory.
